==English==
===Etymology===
From Greek [[ύραξ]] ([[shrew]])

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈhɑɪ.ɹæks/}}

===Noun===
'''hyrax''' (''plural:'' [[hyraxes]] or [[hyraces]])

# any of several small, [[ungulate]] [[herbivorous]] [[mammal]]s, of the [[order]] ''[[Hyracoidea]]'', with a bulky frame and fanglike [[incisor]]s; they are native to [[Africa]] and the [[Middle East]].

